runs.comm: Back and pushed to point.
turned into the leg side off his hip
onto the back foot, into the covers, a tight run and Prior scrambles for home as the throw just misses ... he would have gone as well
cramped for room and he gets no power on a prod to point
slower ball and wide as well, Cook waits ... and waits and then drives the ball past extra cover
punched off the back foot, it evades a diving cover and then accelerates over the cut net pitches and races away
a swish and a miss
booming wide down the leg-side ... a wide in almost any form of the game and Ramdin leaps to his left to gather
snorter, swings through Prior, cutting him in half, and it is taken well down the leg side as it continues to swing after passing the bat
flicked off the front foot on the move, wide of midwicket and four all the way
agricultural ... a step to leg and a heave over the off side. Super, except that he missed!
heaved - he almost pulled himself off his feet - and nobody out at deep square leg
zips through a defensive prod, loud and beseeching appeal but nothing doing. A thin edge ...
good line, just outside off at 88mph (is that right?) and Prior misses with a no-footwork swing
seamed back into Prior at 86mph, he leaps and it takes him on the thigh and into the leg side
tight line, Cook plays it defensively back down the track
Cook had little idea, creasebound and turned square, a deflection off his pads zooms between keeper and slip
no footwork, a poke and a miss. Good bowling, far too good for Cook
super end to a super over ... full, straight and Cook is cleaned up, middle stump left flat on its back
smashes/slogs over extra cover. leans back and thumps it
speared down leg as he sees Prior step to the off, but too much of an adjustment and it's a wide
and again Prior steps to the off, and this time thumps it high over midwicket for full of a length
another steepler lofted over midwicket, into no man's land and safe
very correct defensive push, soft hands, and a quick single as the bowler has to adjust his follow-through to retrieve
short, Prior on the ,move couldn't adjust and it thuds into his midriff
straight, Prior on the walk to leg is beaten all ends up, missing by some way, and his leg stump goes walkies
phew - 90mph and pushed to mid-on
Trott onto the back foot and he can only block to cover
and another post-90mph delivery, pushed wide of mid-on and Trott gets down the safe end
full, almost yorker-length, pushed to short midwicket
one-handed backfoot drive through the covers, a tad too wide and smacked
slower ball - 71mph - and pushed to mid-on
short, Trott attempts a hook and only loops it off the glove down the leg side to Ramdin
drives inches to the right of the diving Bravo at slip ... so close ...
a cry of anguish from Rampaul as Collingwood well beaten and the ball scrapes the stumps
turned square on the leg side
Collingwood tries to turn to get, misses, and gets struck on the pads and he executes a rather girlie jump
nothing remotely feminine about that, shortish and thumped through the leg side
trademark KP pull but it goes rather straighter than intended ... still four
mistimed pull again feet over midwicket as Powell tries to knock Pietersen's block off
loud shout for caught behind but nothing doing as Ramdin cannot quite gather
tight single, out with the hit but mid-off misses
ripper at 89mph, Collingwood beaten all ends up
leg side, clipped through midwicket
a swing and Pietersen almost too early on the drive and he misses
full toss driven straight down the ground
driven to long-off
driven but with no power and the bowler fields ...groans from the crowd
flicked to leg with hands twirling
driven to long-off once more
steps back but cuts into the ground and the ball bobbles through where slip would have been
full, driven to long-off
tame chip off a leading edge back to Sammy - still not easy in this light - and we get the trademark jig from the bowler
cut hard - very hard! - to point
cut deliberately fine and Richards at fine leg makes a right horlicks of it on the run. Sammy gives a real death stare ...
pad-bat to point
head-high no-ball, swished and hit up and down to the keeper, an immediate apology from the bowler ...it hit Collingwood on the hand
gentle chip but into space on the off side
again he starts walking and chips to deepish mid-on
driven to long-off
driven to long-off
loud shout for leg-before but going down the leg side ..
wide and well driven behind square on the off side
pushed to the right of a diving bowler and it just beats him
driven on the full to the sweeper on the off
hit hard at mid-off who stops with a hint of a juggle
steered to Richards at third man
slower, fuller, clipped into the off
swished to leg, two because it was sublimely placed
defensive push into the off, space found again
a prod and a loud celebration from Ramdin who races down the pitch celebrating. Nothing doing ...
pushed through midwicket
flicked down to fine leg
worked behind square on the off
great start, in the blockhole
sweep, top edge, over short fine leg
back and smacked to mid-off
full and hit hard to long-on
driven one bounce at long-on and Powell stops well on the run
Sammy follows the batsman as he steps to leg and cramps him enough to prevent a big hit
enough of the subtlety ...hit straight over long-on
enough of the subtlety ... hit straight over long-on
excellent thinking ... Samuels sees the batsman coming and fires one wide at 78mph, Collingwood stranded and Ramdin takes and whips the bails off
driven with no real va va voom to long-off
pushed into the leg side
easy single again ..but singles not enough
Mascarenhas forced back and all he can do is block ... 87mph
outside off, Mascarenhas pushes limply and misses
bouncer and Mascarenhas ducks ... Powell gives a stare and then jogs back to his mark
a grimace as Powell fires down the leg side
swished off the back foot from outside off into the leg side
sweetly clipped off his toes airily to deep midwicket
bad ball to finish a superb spell, wide and slow and Mascarenhas slashes that over backward point
launches towards cow corner, it plugs in the turf and two men envelope the ball just inside the ropes
there is room for subtlety ... clipped fine on the leg side
full and hammered backward of point with a flourish
Shah dancing in the crease, works to leg and an easy two as the throw from long leg is poor
premeditated paddle-sweep fine, enough to beat the man
off pad, Shah sets off but Mascarenhas going nowhere and he has to scramble back
driven back to Smith, he half stops, it hits Shah but they manage the run
wide full toss, slashed wide of backward point
Shah moves to leg, Smith follows. Good bowling
super stuff, tickled past short fine leg, well placed ...this is classy batting
tip and run to midwicket
massive appeal for leg before, through everyone and it shoots to where long-stop would be ... and it's given as wides to add insult to runs
driven to long-on
slower ball, turned into the leg side, looking for two but Morton on it quickly
flighted, almost too slow for Shah and it thuds into his pads as he goes to leg
heave-pulled wide of short fine leg and to the left of deep square leg ...
rasping drive through extra cover, the fielder has to dive to stop it and that allows them to come back for two
full toss, thumped to long-on
Mascarenhas chips to long-on
turned through midwicket off his hips, no pace on it and that allows the second
swished to backward square leg, only the one as the man was in PDQ
late thick edge, and a deliberate one, Bravo roars round and cuts it off at third man
a real village heave into the leg side, frantic running from batsmen and fielders, the former just win
another big heave square on the leg, too close to the fielder for two
just what the doctor didn't order ... a booming leg-side wide
an almost Pietersenesque swish over midwicket to the man out in the deep
Shah smacks it down the ground to long-on, Mascarenhas races back and beats a poor throw
patted into the leg side, Mascarenhas wants two, Shah knackered
Mascarenhas back., waits and heaves to long-on
that's it, wides down the leg side, Shah swipes and misses but it's academic
